rComments: Ensign's approach to teaching is great!  The variety of bombardment of concepts, facts, and ideas were presented in so many cool engaging ways ranging from guest speakers, slides, class discussions, to presentations.  Really made me value multidimensional stimulation in a classroom setting.

Good exposure to the entrepreneurial process.  We had some very good class discussions.  Seems pretty easy and laid back, but make sure you follow instructions and due dates.  Prof doesn't make the material any harder or complex than it needs to be.  Entrepreneurship:  is it art or science?  Dunno, but a pretty fun class.
Really enjoyed your enthusiasm as a professor, class was much more lively than my typical HR courses. Thanks for the semester!
Most entertaining, relaxed and understanding prof I have ever had in university. Highly recommended

Great prof... Always hyper/excited. Very entertaining and mentions once in a while how he is scared of his wife: "Don't do anything to the car... It's my wife's :-/" LOL   Definitely a class a recommend with this prof!!!! Reading the book will help you get higher than a B but you need to pay attention to small details?... Guest speakers are good

It's my wife's :-/" LOL   Definitely a class a recommend with this prof!!! Reading the book will help you get higher than a B but you need to pay attention to small details?... Funniest prof ever I highly recommend getting him for any class you can. He makes the material so easy and you can get a B without putting in any effort. Some marks are for purely showing up to his class

His lectures are decent (much better than average here) and often lead to class discussion. Attendance is frequently taken. Make certain to buy the book, you will need it for the final exam. Some great guest speakers.  Join in or form a good group for the business plan - your grade in the course depends on it.  TA was  slow to get assignments back.

A great prof. Can't remember clearly but you can get like 20% just by going to class, watch videos and sign the attendance sheet. Really a nice guy, even emailed me after final exam asking me if I attended one of the in class video sessions because the extra 2% could bump me up to A-. Definitely recommended if you are taking ADM 3318
Very funny. Slightly scatterbrained. Book was useless until the final exam - multiple choice questions were from the book. Easy class.

This prof was great... I think he was the most helpful prof I've had in University. He's human unlike so many others at the School of Management. Yes, sometimes we think that he's on crack but it makes it that much more enjoyable to attend! ahaha. You should definitely have him as a prof!
Communicates well!  Great sense of humor.  Level headed.  Positive.  I learn material I can use later on.  I would go have a beer with this professor!
He was a very interesting guy, I think he may be on drugs, but it was fun to watch.

great prof.......i defenitly learned a lot in his lectures, he's very friendly & helpful....what i like about him is the fact that he is frank, he does support public opinion whether it's against or in favour of any business issue......very interactive in class.......MT and Final are all multiple choice, so just read the book and you'll be fine

This prof is great. He will do anything to help you if you show that you want it. Yes, he seems nervous sometimes but really he's one of the most human profs of the School of Management. His lectures...are half interesting. It depends on the day.

Sorry guys but this teacher is horrible.  And I'm saying this as a person who didn't get bad grades in his class.  Basically, HE DOESN'T TEACH YOU ANYTHING.  He's insecure and can't properly answer student questions.  He talks A LOT and says nothing.  And be careful: he pretends to be knowledgeable, but many "facts" he tells you are incorrect.

One of the best classes I have ever taken. The professor keeps the class interesting, although he's always off topic. He always provides real life examples before classes and interesting articles. I don't think anyone will ever complain about this professor. He's great!

the class is very easy.  he really doesn't lecture.  he didn't hand out grade fairly.  should've got 81% in the course and he gave out a C+ instead.  he's reason being 2 of my group members said i didn't do enough work so I got a letter grade and a half lower on all assignments.  come on, he didn't even tell me he was lowering my marks.

This class is easy.  We didn't have that many actual lectures.  Involves mainly group work, real cases, and a final business plan.  The book was virtually useless to the course.  A very fun class!  Its an easy credit.
